        explain: "The parser tried to load a file cited by an `import \"path\"` directive but `read_file` reported the resolved path does not exist. Common causes: typo in the path string, missing file, wrong directory level (`../` count off by one). Paths are resolved relative to the file containing the import, then normalized (./, ../ collapsed). Stage1 punch list Gap 1 — added when the parser learned to recursively load imports instead of treating them as opaque names.",
        fix_it_kind: FixItKind::Replace
