        explain: "The HIR→MIR match-arm lowering currently handles wildcard, ident, enum_path, literal_int, literal_string, and struct_pattern. Any other pattern shape is silently coerced into a general operand-equality test today, which can be wrong (e.g. ranges, or-patterns, struct-field patterns once the parser learns them). Stage1 punch list C10 — emit HX1102 instead of relying on an operand fallback so the missing pattern kind shows up as a diagnostic.",
        fix_it_kind: FixItKind::None
    },
    DiagSpec {
