        explain: "Hexa stage1 lowering currently inlines closure bodies at the call site without environment capture. If a closure references a variable defined in an outer scope, the inline path produces an undefined reference at MIR/LIR time. Stage1 Gap 14.1 follow-up will add closure conversion (environment struct synthesis + indirect call). Until then, rewrite the closure to take all dependencies as explicit parameters, or inline the computation. Severity: Warning so a transient capture does not block the build, but the produced binary may have undefined behaviour for the closure path.",
        fix_it_kind: FixItKind::None
    },
    DiagSpec {
        code: "HX1110",
        title: "host-stdlib import in embedded target",
        severity: Severity::Error,
        stage: "codegen",
        template: "host-stdlib import `{path}` is forbidden under --target=`{target}` (embedded targets only allow stdlib/core, stdlib/alloc, stdlib/hal, stdlib/embedded, stdlib/mcu)",
        explain: "Targets matching `*-none-*` (e.g. thumbv7em-none-eabihf, riscv32imac-unknown-none-elf, thumbv6m-none-eabi) are bare-metal: they have no host OS, no libc, no syscall surface. Importing modules from the host stdlib (stdlib/io, stdlib/http, stdlib/json, ...) under these targets pulls in symbols the firmware linker cannot resolve and breaks the no_std contract documented in SPEC.yaml firmware_evolution. Allowed embedded-safe paths: `stdlib/core/*` (pure: int, slice, option, result, math), `stdlib/alloc/*` (allocator interface), `stdlib/hal/*` (hardware abstraction layer), `stdlib/embedded/*` (panic handler, no_std prelude), `stdlib/mcu/*` (MCU-specific drivers). Phase F3 deliverable: target_gate_check enforcement at compile time.",
        fix_it_kind: FixItKind::Replace
