        explain: "Functions carrying @verify or @law annotations, OR whose body references atlas L[*] nodes, are knowledge-bearing artifacts — they must be bound to atlas L. Cite an existing law with `@implements(L[id])`, or register a new one with `@discover(kind=\"L\")`. Land it upstream via the `hexa atlas` CLI: `hexa atlas register <file.hexa>` writes the proposed shard (compiler/discover/staging.hexa); then `hexa atlas promote --staging <shard>` folds it into the live atlas if you own hexa-lang (the `update` arm — emits atlas.append.<date>.n6, so the atlas grows with every contribution); or `hexa atlas pr` branches + `gh pr create`s against origin (the `PR` arm — non-owners). Bypass while a migration is in flight: `@grace(HX8004, until, reason)` — never silently (every @grace site emits HX9000 and the build is gated on acked-grace consent).",
